olive oil
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
1 onion
1 drizzle soy sauce
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 packet Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 tbs rice wine vinegar
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet Asian Greens
1 packet flat noodles
½ tbs brown sugar (or honey)

• Boil the kettle. Thinly slice carrot into rounds. Trim and halve green beans. Roughly chop red onion and Asian greens.
• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot, green beans and onion with a splash of water, tossing, until tender, 4-6 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and a drizzle of soy sauce and cook, tossing, until wilted,1 minute. Transfer to a bowl.

• While veggies are cooking, place flat noodles in a medium bowl. Add enough boiling water to cover noodles, then set aside until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Stir with a fork to separate. Drain.

• Return frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook diced chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Add ginger lemongrass paste and cook, tossing, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Return veggies to pan, then add noodles, teriyaki sauce, brown sugar, rice wine vinegar and a splash of water. Toss to combine and cook until slightly reduced, 1 minute.

• Divide teriyaki chicken noodles with Asian greens between bowls.
• Top with crushed peanuts.